----------------------------------------------------------------- SSH multiplexing -----------------------------------------------------------
meaning==> SSH multiplexing ka use multiple SSH connections ko reuse karne ke liye hota hai, taaki connection establishment ka time reduce ho sake aur efficiency badh sake.

SSH multiplexing allows you to reuse an existing SSH connection for multiple sessions, instead of creating a new connection every time you SSH into a server. This makes subsequent connections faster.

SSH multiplexing ka use un scenarios mein hota hai jahan tumhare paas multiple SSH connections ek hi remote server ya set of servers ke saath hote hain.

Yeh connection setup time ko significantly reduce karta hai, especially jab tum same server par baar-baar connect kar rahe ho.

It is ideal for automating tasks, cloud infrastructure management, DevOps tasks, and monitoring systems.

==> practical

goto your .ssh directory and create a file config
and also create cm_socket directory where all the active sessions are store.
eg: mkdir -p .ssh/cm_socket
chmod 700 .ssh/cm_socket
vi config and enter those details 
Host server1
  HostName 192.168.159.129   # Yeh remote server ka IP hai
  User root                  # Tumhare username ko root set kar rahe ho
  ControlMaster auto         # Multiplexing enable 
  ControlPath ~/.ssh/cm_socket/%h-%p-%r  # Socket path
  ControlPersist 10m         # Agar tum disconnect ho, toh 10 minutes tak connection open rahega
